
[1]escurial

   ESCU'RIAL, n. The palace or residence of the King of Spain, about 15
   miles North West of Madrid. This is the largest and most superb
   structure in the kingdom, and one of the most splendid in Europe. It is
   built in a dry barren spot,and the name itself is said to signify a
   place full of rocks.

   The Escurial is a famous monastery built by Philip II in the shape of a
   gridiron, in honor of St. Laurence. It takes its name from a village
   near Madrid. It contains the king's palace, St. Laurence's church, the
   monastery of Jerenomites, and the free schools.
